@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home page";
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4">Welcome to Hunter Wolves</h1>
    <p>A place to educate the public about wolves and clear up misconseptions about them.</p>
</div>

<div class="main-body">
    <div class="habitat">
        <h3>Scientific Name:</h3>
        <p>Canis-Lupis</p>
    </div>  
    <div style="display:inline">
        <div class="habitat">
            <h3>Habitats:</h3>        
            <img src="./images/group001.jpg">
            <p>Wolves can thrive in a diversity of habitats from the tundra to woodlands, forests, grasslands and deserts. Wolves are carnivores—they prefer to eat large hoofed mammals such as deer, elk, bison, and moose. They also hunt smaller mammals such as beavers, rodents, and hares.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="reproductive">
        <h3>Wolf Reproduction Facts:</h3>
        <p>Who reproduces in a wolf pack?
Usually only the dominant pair breeds, however in areas where there is a high ratio of prey per wolf, such as in Yellowstone National Park, there can be multiple litters per pack.</p>
    </div>  
    <div class="culture">
        <h3>Wolves in Popular Culture:</h3>
        <img src="./images/movie001.jpg">
        <p>Wolves have been featured in books, fairy tales, cartoons, and movies </p>
    </div>
</div>



